Users who require real-time access to NOAA and Navy model fields are directed to the high-availability servers at NCEP:  http://www.opc.ncep.noaa.gov/newNCOM/NCOM_currents.shtml
To improve the ability to meet the growing demand for high-value environmental data and information, NOAA&#039;s existing three National Data Centers - the National Climatic Data Center, the National Geophysical Data Center, and the National Oceanographic Data Center (including the National Coastal Data Development Center) have merged into the National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI).</r3d:remarks>
